Goerge,
I think your main challenge will end up being one in which you need to have
the notion of a uniform interface in your solution. I&#39;d be curious to know
how you plan to map that to a binary protocol. The Uri mapping problem is
the easy part. Like Sebastien said,

as long as the server is responsible for telling you if dereferencing of the
opaque identifier was successful, a.k.a. as long as there is no assumption
from the client that the ip / port combination is resolvable / exists.

... you should be fine if you follow that tenet.

Best,
-Dilip



